ely get involved in these matters, I did send feedback on this issue to Verant a few weeks ago.<br>
<br>
The problem with pets and aggro is teh same one as having lower-level players tagging along on major raids.  The scoop:<br>
<br>
Every monster, in its aggro radius (which is often larger than it appears) has a percentage chance to notice a player coming into its radius.  This percentage increases based on two components: relative closeness, and the level of the player.  Ergo, people can sometimes &quot;level pull&quot; social creatures from a group and still not gain aggro on the other creatures.  (This is an individual mob's aggro working in conjunction with the chain aggro effect of passing hate to other creatures.)<br>
<br>
Now, a magician summoning a pet remains neutral to all other creatures until he sends in that pet to attack.  Once it engages and gets on a hate list, its lower level means that teh creatures engaging in it are more likely to broadcast a wider awarenes of its presence (just as if you had a level 49 player attacking on a raid that was comprised of mostly 55th level characters).<br>
<br>
This was tested in a number of areas.. from lower levls such as in teh back courtyard of mistmoore, to at higher levels a pet's effects on teh ledge in the Halls of Testing.  On teh ledge,m sans pet, we could single pull.  The second I summoned a pet (in teh middle fo a battle, and teh pet was fighting in relative position BEHIND ME) it nonetheless pulled teh other pit mob and from there two other MOBS by chain aggro.<br>
<br>
In tight dungeons (such as doing lower levels of Chardok) where aggro control is crucial, a pet cn sadly be considered a hindrance because of its aggro raidus issues once it attacks.  <br>
<br>
The solution would be similar to teh solution they have done for pet resists: For purposes of aggro only, have pets effectively create aggro equal to the level of their caster.<br>
<br>
It is a somewhat complicated issue to explain, but one that can once again create teh cries of &quot;no pets!&quot; during raids when pets could remain very useful tools otherwise.<br>
<br>
