<br>
The following examples make me believe without a doubt that this exists.<br>
<br>
• Our party just surfaced out of the water after killing the mini burrower in Acrylia, and as the we disposed of the couple grimlings sitting up on the shore, I summoned my pet out of the water to assist. The second my pet began attacking, two grimlings from the above platform (out of aggro range) rushed down to my pet, while a conjurer kept chain nuking me. Again, these three grimlings directly attacked <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> only</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> my pet or myself until someone taunted them off of me. I was not creating any means of aggro at the time by sitting or nuking, I only sent my pet in.<br>
<br>
• Our party was headed to the assassins room in Ssra to kill the commander and get a kitty mask. We rushed one side as we entered the room, and after I sent my pet in, the snake on the other side of the room (same elevation) aggroed from far out of melee range, and came directly after me. Same as before, I was not sitting or nuking, I only sent my pet in.<br>
<br>
There are many other occasions that have lead me to believe pets have a larger &quot;aggro radius&quot; (see opening statement), but these recent events are far fresher in my mind. Spew all the technical crap you want to, but I live life (and play games) using my own experience, and through that experience, I believe this is an issue. <p><br><center><font face="tahoma, verdana" size="1">[ <b>Baron</b> | <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=90407" target="blank">Odibil Lauxes</a> | <b>Arch Mage</b> ]<br>Pain and Suffering tries to strike YOU, but misses!</font></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uuaellaen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Uaellaen</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.obenaus.de/germanflag.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 82<br> <font color=#333333>(8/26/02 9:47:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=304.topic&index=9>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.amm-electronics.net/Everquest/UaellaenMesana.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Left Undone: Pet Aggro radius</span><hr size=1> i belive its an issue too ... easy fix .. increase my pet lvl <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   i miss the days where my pet conned even or YELLOW!!!  <p>[ 60 Arch Mage ] <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=156616" > 
