<br>
Before the recent changes, my faction work in Droga was complicated by the fact that I had to pull goblins one by one to keep pet from getting overwhelmed too quickly.  After the changes, I send pet straight into a room of them and they don't care.  Sure, they heal if they can, but they don't attack my pet anymore.  Made life much much easier in Droga.<br>
<br>
In Ssra, 3rd floor Emp key camp...killing imperial guards and the like...we pull stuff to one corner.  Pathing normally makes my pet run out towards middle and back in towards the corner to re-engage mob.  No instances of chaining aggro *ever*.  These snakes are all 60, except for the named (go figure, they're harder but con lower...)<br>
